• no sharp attacks — everything swells in and out, like breath;  
• harmony: modal, ambiguous — E minor with added 9ths and suspended 4ths, but blurred by analog drift;  
• mix: ultra-wet (spring reverb, tape delay), but **voice remains dry and central** — as if the singer is the only real thing in a dissolving world;  
• dynamic space: midrange (300–800Hz) left completely open for the raw, low, fry-heavy baritone — the voice cuts through the haze like a flashlight in fog;  
• no climax, no resolution — just slow decay into silence, as if the world evaporated.

